By Liu Yang, Tang Ming, Guo Qi

Editor | Huashi

"
Introduction

On New Year's Eve, my friend circle is almost all about Wuhan Epidemic News, in the crowd all sorts of pictures, gossip, folk appeal, surging and chaotic emotions coexist. Yesterday's entertainment magazine, an oral, with a less comprehensive but no false perspective, describes the day of the city of Wuhan Ordinary People's story. Today, we are trying to get in touch with three friends whose family members are Wuhan frontline or non-frontline hospital workers, asking them to describe from the perspective of bystanders some of the basic situations faced by frontline medical staff. Again, this is not news reporting, it's just dictation, and there may even be conflicting information. This in turn can reflect the different people because of different channels, and location, the magnitude of the information provided and the authenticity of the difference. Entertainment just wants to make the voices of more individuals in the city, or the frontline, heard by people outside the city in the form of a story. Although they are now being told that medical staff are not allowed to give random interviews, in any form.

According to Entertainment Magazine's usual practice, the Spring Festival gala commentary was launched on the first day of the Lunar New Year, but in consideration of the actual situation, today, the Spring Festival gala commentary of Entertainment Magazine was launched with Pictures and texts.

"

Liu Yang
Aunt: front-line workers in Tongji Hospital

A big part of the reason doctors expose infections,
A lot of people lie about their medical history
————————————————

My home is near the x hospital, aunt is Tongji Hospital medical staff, she is more understanding of the current situation on the front line.

On the 20th, when the central government found out the real situation in Wuhan, it immediately began to deal with the epidemic here. At present, almost all the relevant doctors who could be mobilized have been arranged to visit designated hospitals, and isolation hospitals have also been started to be built. The situation in Wuhan is still very bad. However, the related epidemic news which spreads wildly on the network, some can not be credulous.

It was hard for the doctors, working for days in the most dangerous quarantine zone on what was supposed to be a happy New Year's Eve, a family reunion. A certain sense of moral kidnapping, physical and psychological insecurity, and super-high load of operation, so that they issued even "unsustainable" feeling, completely understandable. However, some of the information spread abroad is exaggerated, and even have the suspicion of fraud. Fixed-point hospital doctors exposed to infection, but the net Tongji Hospital was infected by the death of a doctor, completely false. My Aunt told me that the man had been doing squatting the day before he died. A large part of the reason why doctors exposed the infection was that a large number of citizens had previously lied about their medical history, saying they had never been to south China seafood city, but in fact they had contracted pneumonia by then, and doctors had let down their guard and come into contact with them, easily becoming infected.

The change came on the 20th, the day CCTV published its article, the day the Central Government got hold of the real situation in Wuhan. What happened here has been kept under wraps for too long. On the 20th, the city was taken over by the central government, which was directly involved in the prevention and control of Wuhan's new pneumonia. Now the doctor's protective gear is being fine-tuned.

But for now, at least, most doctors are on their own, and there is no way to appeal for outside help. At the beginning of the site was not fully set up, so there are many suspected patients are there, gold and Silver Pool Hospital directly to receive Concorde fever patients. There's no denying that the last few days have been horrible, untenable. The first supplies arrived at 8:00 yesterday, New Year's Eve. As of today, supplies are arriving. The front-line medics were devastated when the supplies and personnel failed to arrive last night.

I have a little more news to add. Aunties say many of the little nurses around them travel to work, which is a big problem. Public transportation was canceled, no private cars, and I borrowed an electric car from a friend. The hospital does not have the special car to send, the folk spontaneous organization sends and sends the medical personnel, is not very comprehensive.

Tang Ming
PARENTS: Central Theater Command is not a front line job

The biggest problem right now is the lack of medical supplies
————————————————

Wuhan was closed, leaving ten million people in fear, as was I, but I was already one of the safe majority. To save my life, I locked myself in the house every day, trying to isolate all possible sources of infection. Although my home was in the hospital, it wouldn't be a big problem if I didn't go out, i am always worried about my parents'safety. My heart told me that it was too dangerous to let mom and dad walk into the clinic again, but my mind beat me, too, and they had to be the front line soldiers in the place of saving lives.

My parents work in the Central Theater Command General Hospital, which is just a general hospital, not the new pneumonia designated hospital in Wuchang District. If there are suspected cases, patients will be advised to seven hospitals or other designated hospitals for treatment, general hospitals refused to accept and treat patients with fever, but non-designated hospital doctors did not go home, on call, to the beginning of the shift. My mother worked in the pediatric clinic, and in addition to taking care of their own, they could be part of an emergency medical team, a combat readiness medical team, ready to go to war in the event of an emergency.

Mom and Dad told me that many of their friends work in designated hospitals, the front line of the battle with "chaos and chaos" to describe, never too much. The biggest problem now, as the Internet has revealed, is that medical supplies are running low and not keeping up with demand: There are no protective clothing, only plain white coats; medical surgical masks can only be used by out-patient doctors and those involved in surgery, the only thing left for the rest of the staff were plain face masks. The N95, which had been snapped up by the outside world, did not exist. The doctors and nurses were almost directly exposed to the hospital, with no contact with the patients. Dad With the Department of colleagues to follow the ambulance team to the designated hospital support, the initial did not have goggles. As a result, the colleague, who had been running a fever, is now classified as a suspected case and has been quarantined.

From my parents'description, I understand that the current situation is that the total number of fever clinics in Wuchang District is seriously inadequate and overloaded, and that the medical resources of designated hospitals are in short supply, both in terms of hardware and software. There's a long line at seven hospitals, and there may not be room. Some projects even require an all-night Queue. Mild cases of suspected cases of hospital has not enough space to give them isolation, can only go home to take their own isolation.

We are most concerned about the kit, at present there is no general hospital, fixed-point hospital also exists the problem of inadequate kit, online heat transfer of this situation is indeed true. Not only outside of Wuhan, we receive information every day of the epidemic, the city we are the same. Whether the messages are true or not, some of them are even shared by local doctors. As far as I know, the lack of supplies at the hospital is closer to the truth.

Some doctors had to travel from Hankou to Wuchang, and without private cars they could only call taxis or Didi, which are now closed on even and odd numbers. In order to make it easier for doctors to get to the hospital, the government is equipped with a special transport vehicle. In addition to local doctors, these two days also have Beijing, Shanghai medical team to designated hospitals to the fever clinic support.

Guo Qi
UNCLE: Hubei Provincial People's Hospital, now temporarily transferred to the gold and Silver Tan hospital

Eat instant noodles clean AH, now buy cooked food can not be sure whether health
——————————————————————

Like everyone else, a lot of what's going around the Internet, I can't be sure. However, the news that the medical staff ate instant noodles last night seemed to me quite normal. I learned from my uncle that the supplies from Tongji Hospital had indeed arrived, and everyone in Tongji Xiehe ate instant noodles. It's clean. You don't know if it's sanitary to buy cooked food. At the very least, the instant noodles are wrapped in plastic.

Early this morning, the uncle was called away, under the age of 35 were transferred to the gold and Silver Tan, "old guys" sit in this hospital. There's a critical shortage of medical staff. We're running low on staff at the Wuchang Regional Hospitals, so we're starting to move the staff from the other districts. If the people who go to gold and Silver Tan "DIE IN BATTLE" , the next batch of people continue to take the top.


It's hard for the paramedics, it's hard for the police. The army doesn't take holidays. Yesterday, the army doctors have already assembled, the first supplies should arrive today, and the first doctors from all over the country have also assembled and will arrive soon. But the kit, according to my uncle, wasn't enough. There are too many suspected patients in the surrounding area. Do you think 10w will be enough? It's not gonNA hold for a few days. And the Hazmat suits. Not Enough. The News said a doctor wears a diaper, just in case it contaminates the last suit. It's not made up.

(the names are pseudonyms. Instructor: Wu Changchang)
